## Summary

Implements B28 — Tier-0 enforcement on every PR across all three BytePort engines.

## Changes

- **New: `.github/workflows/tier-0-gate.yml`** — blocking CI gate enforcing:
  - Go: `go build`, `go test`, `go vet`, `go fmt` (blocking), `golangci-lint`
  - Rust: `cargo build`, `cargo fmt --check`, `cargo clippy -D warnings`
  - Frontend (SvelteKit): `npm run build`, `prettier --check`, `eslint`, `svelte-check`

## What changed from existing CI

| Check | Before | After |
|---|---|---|
| Go fmt | `continue-on-error: true` (advisory) | Blocking |
| Rust build/test/lint | Not enforced | Blocking via cargo |
| Frontend build/typecheck | Not enforced | Blocking via npm |
| Rust go lint (`clippy -D warnings`) | Not enforced | Blocking |
| `quality-gate.yml` | No-op placeholder | Replaced by tier-0-gate.yml |

## Constraints

- `phenotype-sdk` is explicitly excluded (org policy)
- Concurrency: one run per ref; new commits cancel in-flight runs
- Timeouts: 30m per job

## Testing

- [ ] CI must pass on this PR before merge
- [ ] All existing workflows continue unchanged

Refs: B28
